work.name: SMALL REU, Williams College
work.summary: Worked on multiple research projects, including: developing a novel, structurally distinct variant of the Zeckendorf Game; significantly improving the algorithm for Zeckendorf vector decomposition; formulating a new additive uncertainty principle and substantially strengthening recovery conditions for missing signal frequencies; and implementing and analyzing a novel setup for a signal recovery problem that outperforms existing approaches.

projects.name: Quantum Computing
projects.summary: Quantum computing is the use of quantum-mechanical phenomena such as superposition and entanglement to perform computation. Computers that perform quantum computations are known as quantum computers.
